Sentencas: Single layer La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3 hollow fibre (HF) precursors (< 1 mm ID) produced by phase inversion (PI) were sintered at 1,200, 1,350 and 1,400 A degrees C.
Titulo: Effects of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cathode properties on hollow fibre micro-tubular SOFC performances

Sentencas: The increase in sintering temperature resulted in microstructural changes in the LSCF fibres, reflected in their electrical conductivities.
Titulo: Effects of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cathode properties on hollow fibre micro-tubular SOFC performances

Sentencas: LSCF-based cathodes with different designs were brushed onto co-extruded nickel-gadolinium-doped ceria (CGO) anode/CGO electrolyte dual-layer HFs (< 1 mm ID) fabricated by PI.
Titulo: Effects of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cathode properties on hollow fibre micro-tubular SOFC performances

Sentencas: The effect of cathode layers on the overall performance of the fuel cells (FCs) was assessed using nearly identical anode and electrolyte compositions, thicknesses, and microstructures.
Titulo: Effects of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cathode properties on hollow fibre micro-tubular SOFC performances

Sentencas: Cathode microstructure design caused cells to perform differently producing peak power densities of 0.35-0.7 W cm(-2) at 600 A degrees C. Impedance spectroscopy analysis at 600 A degrees C on the FCs produced 0.12-0.24 Omega cm(2) confirming the cathode's structural effect on the overall area-specific resistance of the FCs.
Titulo: Effects of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cathode properties on hollow fibre micro-tubular SOFC performances

Sentencas: The best performing FC with a brush-deposited cathode was compared to a similar FC where cathode was deposited by dip coating; at 600 A degrees C the first produced 0.6 W cm(-2) while the second cell 0.7 W cm(-2).
Titulo: Effects of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cathode properties on hollow fibre micro-tubular SOFC performances

Sentencas: Co-extruding anodes and electrolytes by using PI and combining dip coating for cathode deposition could lead to the fabrication of FCs with enhanced microstructures and improved performances.
Titulo: Effects of lanthanum strontium cobalt ferrite (LSCF) cathode properties on hollow fibre micro-tubular SOFC performances
